      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## 🎉 URL Into Selection v1.11.2 - Enhanced Stability & User Experience\r\n\r\nThis release consolidates several improvements focused on fixing false positives, enhancing URL detection, and improving the overall user experience.\r\n\r\n### 🐛 Bug Fixes\r\n- **Fixed various false positives** that were incorrectly triggering URL transformation (#39, #40)\r\n- **Updated manifest description** to better clarify markdown link creation functionality (#55)\r\n- **Prevented unwanted angle brackets** when pasting URLs inside existing markdown links (#64)\r\n- **Resolved critical bugs** and improved codebase structure for better maintainability\r\n\r\n### ✨ Recent Features (v1.9.0 - v1.11.0)\r\n- **Preserve Obsidian wikilinks**: Selected text is now preserved as alias when pasting wikilinks (#56)\r\n- **Smart command rejection**: Plugin now ignores command-like text and configuration patterns (#58)\r\n- **Quote stripping**: Automatic removal of quotes from file paths and URLs for cleaner results (#60)\r\n\r\n### 🏗️ Under the Hood\r\n- Comprehensive refactoring for improved code quality and maintainability\r\n- Enhanced URL detection patterns with better edge case handling\r\n- Improved paste event handling to reduce conflicts with other plugins\r\n\r\n### 📦 Installation\r\nDownload the latest release files (`main.js` and `manifest.json`) and place them in your `.obsidian/plugins/url-into-selection/` folder.\r\n\r\n---\r\n*This plugin enhances Obsidian's URL pasting by automatically creating markdown links when you paste URLs into selected text - just like in Notion\\!*",
